4418|c=Category:Meghan, Duchess of Sussex|the Duchess of Sussex|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|s=no|wikt=no|n=no|q=Meghan, Duchess of Sussex}}\n* {{official website|https://sussexroyal.com/}}\n* [https://www.royal.uk/duchess-sussex The Duchess of Sussex] at the official website of the British royal family\n* [https://www.princeofwales.gov.uk/duke-and-duchess-sussex The Duke and Duchess of Sussex profile] at the official website of the [[Prince of Wales]]\n* {{IMDb name|1620783|Meghan Markle}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-prec|uk}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge|The Duchess of Cambridge]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United Kingdom order of precedence|Ladies]]<br /> '''''The Duchess of Sussex''''' }}\n{{s-fol|after=[[Autumn Phillips]]}}\n{{end}}\n{{Meghan, Duchess of Sussex}}\n{{Navboxes\n|list=\n{{British princesses by marriage}}\n{{UK Order of Precedence (Ladies)}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Royalty|United Kingdom|United States}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meghan, Duchess of Sussex}}\n[[Category:Meghan, Duchess of Sussex| ]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women]]\n[[Category:20th-century Protestants]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women]]\n[[Category:21st-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Hollywood, Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Immaculate Heart High School, Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American Anglicans]]\n[[Category:American calligraphers]]\n[[Category:American emigrants to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:American expatriate actresses in Canada]]\n[[Category:American feminists]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:British baronesses|Kilkeel]]\n[[Category:British countesses|Dumbarton]]\n[[Category:British duchesses by marriage|Sussex]]\n[[Category:British feminists]]\n[[Category:Converts to Anglicanism]]\n[[Category:Game show models]]\n[[Category:House of Windsor]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Markle family|Meghan]]\n[[Category:Mountbatten-Windsor family]]\n[[Category:Northwestern University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from View Park\u2013Windsor Hills, California]]\n[[Category:Wives of British princes]]\n[[Category:Women calligraphers]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{short description|American actress, wife of Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex}}\n{{Infobox royalty\n| name               = Meghan\n| title              = [[Duke of Sussex|Duchess of Sussex]] ([[#Titles, styles, and arms|more]])<!--full titles not needed here-->\n| image              = Meghan Markle - 2018 (cropped).jpg <!--to avoid an incipient edit war, get consensus on talk to change the picture-->\n| caption            = Meghan in 2018\n| birth_name         = Rachel Meghan Markle\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1981|8|4|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Los Angeles]], California, U.S.\n| spouse             = {{plainlist|\n* {{marriage|[[Trevor Engelson]]|September 10, 2011|August 2013|end=divorced}}\n* {{marriage|[[Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex]]|May 19, 2018}}\n}}\n| issue            = [[Archie Mountbatten-Windsor]]\n| house            = [[House of Windsor|Windsor]] (by marriage)<!--See [[Talk:House of Windsor#SHSG Part II]]-->\n| father           = [[Thomas Markle]]\n| mother           = [[Doria Ragland]]\n| occupation       = Actress (2002\u20132017)\n| signature        = Signature of the HRH Meghan, Duchess of Sussex.svg\n}}\n{{British Royal Family}}\n\n'''Meghan, Duchess of Sussex''' (born '''Rachel Meghan Markle'''; August 4, 1981) is an American former actress and the wife of [[Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex]].\n\nMarkle was raised in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. During her studies at [[Northwestern University]], she began playing small roles in television series and films. From 2011 to 2017, she played [[Rachel Zane]] on the American legal drama ''[[Suits (American TV series)|Suits]]''. She is an outspoken feminist and has addressed issues of [[gender inequality]], and her lifestyle website ''The Tig'' featured a column profiling influential women. She represented international charity organizations and received recognition for her fashion and style, releasing a line of clothing in 2016.\n\nMarkle was married to actor and producer [[Trevor Engelson]] from 2011 until their divorce in 2013. In 2017, she announced her engagement to [[Prince Harry]], grandson of [[Queen Elizabeth II]], and she moved to London. She retired from acting, closed her related social media accounts, and started undertaking public engagements as part of the British royal family. She became [[Duke of Sussex|Duchess of Sussex]] upon [[Wedding of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle|her marriage]] to [[Prince Harry]] in 2018. They have a son, [[Archie Mountbatten-Windsor]]. In 2020, the couple announced [[Megxit|their intention to step back]] as senior members of the royal family and split their time between the UK and North America.\n\n==Early life==\n{{See also|Family of the Duchess of Sussex}}\nRachel Meghan Markle<ref name=birthindex>{{cite web|url= http://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/rachel_meghan_markle_born_1981_14988531|title=The Birth of Rachel Markle| publisher=[[California Birth Index]]|accessdate=October 27, 2019|quote=Rachel Meghan Markle was born on August 4, 1981, in Los Angeles County, California. Her father's last name is Markle, and her mother's maiden name is Ragland.}}</ref> was born August 4, 1981, in [[Los Angeles]], California.<ref name=biography.com>{{cite web|url= https://www.biography.com/royalty/meghan-markle|title=Meghan Markle (1981\u2013)|publisher=[[Biography.com]]|accessdate= October 27, 2019|archivedate=September 23, 2019|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20190923065924/https://www.biography.com/royalty/meghan-markle|url-status=live}}</ref> Her mother, [[Doria Ragland]], is a former social worker and yoga instructor living in [[View Park\u2013Windsor Hills, California]].<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |last1=Boyle |first1=Danny |title=Who is Meghan Markle? Everything we know about Prince Harry's girlfriend |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/31/who-is-meghan-markle-everything-we-know-about-the-suits-actress/ |work=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=November 8, 2016 |accessdate=November 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112080658/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/31/who-is-meghan-markle-everything-we-know-about-the-suits-actress/ |archivedate=November 12, 2016}} {{subscription}}</ref><ref name=\"bbcnewsmorrismeghanwho\">{{cite news |last1=Morris |first1=Regan |title='Meghan who?' LA shrugs over Harry's hometown girlfriend |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-41391607 |accessdate=November 28, 2017 |publisher=BBC News |date=September 27, 2017 |quote=But Markle's mother lives in the View Park-Windsor Hills neighbourhood, which is one of the wealthiest, primarily African American areas in the US. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930195924/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-41391607 |archivedate=September 30, 2017 |df=}}</ref> Markle has often been described as having a very close friendship with her mother.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/05/19/europe/doria-ragland-meghan-markle-mother-intl/index.html |title=Doria Ragland: Meghan Markle's mother by her side on wedding day |first=Angela |last=Dewan |work=CNN |access-date=May 31, 2018}}</ref> Her father, [[Thomas Markle|Thomas Markle Sr.]], lives in [[Rosarito, Mexico]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Meghan Markle\u2019s father lives in a quiet Baja town; but the British paparazzi have come knocking|work=Los Angeles Times|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-meghan-markle-baja-20180401-story.html |date=May 5, 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180505031834/http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-meghan-markle-baja-20180401-story.html |archivedate=May 5, 2018 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"thetimesmeghanmarklesfamilytree\">{{cite news |last1=Humphries |first1=Will |title=Meghan Markle's family tree |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/meghan-markle-s-family-tree-kvlzmz82s |accessdate=November 28, 2017 |work=[[The Times]]|location=London |date=November 27, 2017}} {{subscription}}</ref> and is a retired television director of photography and lighting director whose profession resulted in his young daughter often visiting the set of ''[[Married...with Children]]''.<ref name=\"Esquire\">{{cite web |url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/tv/a23925/meghan-markle-interview/ |title=Meghan Markle Talks Suits, Catholic Childhood and Growing Up On Set of Married With Children |date=July 13, 2013 |first=Matt |last=Goulet |work=Esquire |publisher=Hearst Communications, Inc. |accessdate=January 14, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227230400/http://www.esquire.com/entertainment/interviews/a23925/meghan-markle-interview/ |archivedate=February 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hicks |first=Tony |title=Prince Harry ready to meet Meghan Markle's father |url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2016/11/11/prince-harry-ready-to-meet-meghan-markles-father/ |work=[[Mercury News]] |date=November 1, 2016 |accessdate=November 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112094556/http://www.mercurynews.com/2016/11/11/prince-harry-ready-to-meet-meghan-markles-father/ |archivedate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> Markle's parents divorced when she was six years old.<ref name=\"Time-Earlylife\">{{cite news |url=http://time.com/5037786/meghan-markle-prince-harry-engagement/ |title=Meet Meghan Markle, Prince Harry's Fiancee And Britain's Newest Royal-To-Be |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |first=Tara |last=John |date=November 27, 2017 |accessdate=November 30, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171128224356/http://time.com/5037786/meghan-markle-prince-harry-engagement/ |archivedate=November 28, 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"half-sister\">{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/books/news/meghan-markles-half-sister-write-tell-all-book-pushy-sibling/ |title=Meghan Markle's half-sister to write a tell-all book about her 'pushy' sibling |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |date=April 3, 2017 |accessdate=November 30, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611193328/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/books/news/meghan-markles-half-sister-write-tell-all-book-pushy-sibling/ |archivedate=June 11, 2017 |df=}}</ref> Her older paternal half-siblings are [[Samantha Markle]] and [[Family of Meghan, Duchess of Sussex#Thomas Markle Jr.|Thomas Markle Jr.]], from whom she is reportedly estranged.<ref name=\"estranged\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/may/15/the-royal-in-laws-meghan-markles-family |title=The royal in-laws: Meghan Markle's family |newspaper=The Guardian |date=May 15, 2018 |accessdate=July 10, 2018 |first=Caroline |last=Davies}}</ref>\n\nMarkle is descended on her mother's side from [[Slavery in the United States|enslaved Africans]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Meghan Markle's Jonesboro roots |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/meghan-markles-jonesboro-roots-q2pkszldq |work=The Times|location=London|accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref> and on her father's side from European settlers.<ref name=DeutscheWelle>{{cite web |url=http://www.dw.com/en/tracing-meghan-markles-german-roots/a-41574493 |title=Tracing Meghan Markle's 'German roots' |work=[[Deutsche Welle]] |date=May 11, 2018 |access-date=May 23, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"The Hastings Connection\">{{cite web |last1=Child |first1=Christopher |title=The Hastings Connection |url=https://vita-brevis.org/2017/12/hastings-connection/#more-9916 |publisher=New England Historic Genealogical Society |date=December 15, 2017 |accessdate=December 16, 2017 |quote=As Gary Boyd Roberts indicated in his press release, 'Meghan Markle is related to Prince Harry hundreds of times over' |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216091604/https://vita-brevis.org/2017/12/hastings-connection/#more-9916 |archivedate=December 16, 2017 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theweek.co.uk/78126/meghan-markle-six-things-you-didnt-know-about-prince-harrys-girlfriend |work=The Week |title=Meghan Markle: Six things you didn't know about Prince Harry's girlfriend |date=November 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110235600/http://www.theweek.co.uk/78126/meghan-markle-six-things-you-didnt-know-about-prince-harrys-girlfriend |archivedate=November 10, 2016}}</ref> She described her heritage in a 2015 essay for ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' magazine: \"My dad is [[White Americans|Caucasian]] and my mom is [[African American]]. I'm half black and half white&nbsp;.... While my mixed heritage may have created a grey area surrounding my self-identification, keeping me with a foot on both sides of the fence, I have come to embrace that. To say who I am, to share where I'm from, to voice my pride in being a strong, confident mixed-race woman.\"<ref name=ElleUK2015-08-17a>{{cite web |last=Markle |first=Meghan |title=I'm More Than An 'Other' |url=http://www.elleuk.com/life-and-culture/news/a26855/more-than-an-other/ |work=Elle UK |date=August 17, 2015 |accessdate=November 4, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104115244/http://www.elleuk.com/life-and-culture/news/a26855/more-than-an-other/ |archivedate=November 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\nMarkle grew up in Hollywood.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-41391607 |title='Meghan who?' LA shrugs over Harry's hometown girlfriend |last1=Morris |first1=Regan |publisher=BBC |date=September 26, 2017 |accessdate=October 26, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026054121/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-41391607 |archivedate=October 26, 2017}}</ref> She was educated at private schools, beginning at age two at the Hollywood Little Red Schoolhouse.<ref>{{cite web |title=Duchess of Sussex \u2013 Education |url=https://www.royal.uk/duchess-sussex |publisher=UK Gov. 2018 |accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Woustra |first1=Kristy |title=Who Is Meghan Markle: The Actress Was Changing The World At Age 11 |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2016/11/11/who-is-meghan-markle_n_12914342.html |work=HuffPost |location=Canada |accessdate=November 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112215502/http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2016/11/11/who-is-meghan-markle_n_12914342.html |archivedate=November 12, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Nick News with Linda Ellerbee]]'' profiled her successful campaign at age 11 to get [[Procter & Gamble]] to change a national television commercial that she viewed as sexist.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/tv/tv-guy/os-et-meghan-markle-at-12-fighting-sexism-on-tv-20171130-story.html |title=Meghan Markle at 11: Fighting sexism on TV |last=Boedeker |first=Hal |date=November 30, 2017 |work=[[Orlando Sentinel]] |access-date=December 1, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201063734/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/tv/tv-guy/os-et-meghan-markle-at-12-fighting-sexism-on-tv-20171130-story.html |archivedate=December 1, 2017 |df=}}</ref> Raised as a Protestant,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/08/europe/meghan-markle-baptized-intl/index.html |title=Meghan Markle baptized in private ceremony |work=CNN |first=Lauren |last=Said-Moorhouse |date=March 9, 2018 |accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref> she nonetheless attended [[Immaculate Heart High School (Los Angeles)|Immaculate Heart High School]], an all-girl Catholic private school in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/05/16/us/meghan-markle-high-school/index.html |title=This is what Meghan Markle's high school teacher remembers most about her |publisher=CNN |first=Mallory |last=Simon |first2=Jason |last2=Carroll |date=May 17, 2018 |accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref> Markle was then admitted to [[Northwestern University]], where she joined [[Kappa Kappa Gamma]] sorority and participated in community service and charity projects.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Swartz |first1=Tracy |title=New Meghan Markle book rehashes time at Northwestern |url=https://www.pressreader.com/usa/chicago-tribune/20180417/281578061253320 |accessdate=April 21, 2018 |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=April 17, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Swartz\"/> She also served an internship at the American embassy in [[Buenos Aires]],<ref name=telegraph>{{cite news |last1=Willgress |first1=Lydia |last2=Boyle |first2=Danny |date=September 21, 2017 |title=Who is Meghan Markle? Everything we know about Prince Harry's girlfriend |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/31/who-is-meghan-markle-everything-we-know-about-the-suits-actress/ |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=April 22, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107023113/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/31/who-is-meghan-markle-everything-we-know-about-the-suits-actress/ |archivedate=January 7, 2017}}</ref> and studied for one semester in [[Madrid]].<ref name=\"Swartz\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/chicagoinc/ct-ent-meghan-markle-northwestern-20180509-story.html |title=Meghan Markle recalled as dignified, charitable during her Northwestern days |last=Swartz |first=Tracy |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=May 9, 2018 |access-date=May 13, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>  She earned her bachelor's degree from Northwestern's [[Northwestern University School of Communication|School of Communication]] in 2003, with a [[Double majors in the United States|double major]] in theater and international studies.<ref>{{cite news |title=Meghan Markle exclusive: Diana's biographer Andrew Morton on how the Suits star made it to the heart of the Establishment |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/meghan-markle-exclusive-dianas-biographer-andrew-morton-on-how-the-suits-star-made-it-to-the-heart-of-the-establishment-cgp0fc86l |work=The Times|location=London |date=April 1, 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180404122637/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/meghan-markle-exclusive-dianas-biographer-andrew-morton-on-how-the-suits-star-made-it-to-the-heart-of-the-establishment-cgp0fc86l |archivedate=April 4, 2018 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref><ref name = telegraph />\n\n==Acting==\nEarly in her career, Markle worked as a freelance [[calligrapher]] and taught [[bookbinding]] to support herself between acting jobs.<ref name=\"Esquire\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/royals/meghan-markle-just-received-a-custom-gift-for-archie-during-a-surprise-outing-in-africa/|title=Meghan Markle Just Received a Custom Gift for Archie During a Surprise Outing in Africa|magazine=People|first=Stephanie|last=Petit|first2=Simon|last2=Perry|date=September 30, 2019|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref> Her first on-screen appearance was a small role as a nurse in an episode of the daytime soap opera ''[[General Hospital]]''.<ref name=\"ABC SID\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.abc.soapsindepth.com/posts/meghan-markle-on-general-hospital-147566 |title=Meghan Markle Started Her Acting Career on ''General Hospital'' |journal=[[Soaps In Depth#ABC Soaps In Depth|ABC Soaps In Depth]] |date=December 5, 2017 |first=Chris |last=Eades |accessdate=January 26, 2018 |publisher=[[Bauer Media Group|Bauer Publications]] |location=United States |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230215554/http://www.abc.soapsindepth.com/posts/meghan-markle-on-general-hospital-147566 |archivedate=December 30, 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"Vulture\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.vulture.com/2017/11/meghan-markles-tv-work-a-guide.html |title=Beyond ''Suits'': Your Guide to Meghan Markle's TV Work |last=Ivie |first=Devon |date=November 28, 2017 |website=[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]]|access-date=November 28, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171129230634/http://www.vulture.com/2017/11/meghan-markles-tv-work-a-guide.html|archive-date=November 29, 2017|url-status=live |df=}}</ref> Markle had small guest roles on the television shows ''[[Century City (TV series)|Century City]]'' (2004), ''[[The War at Home (TV series)|The War at Home]]'' (2006), and ''[[CSI: NY]]'' (2006).<ref name=\"Vulture\" /> She also took on several contract acting and modeling jobs, including a stint as a \"briefcase girl\" on the US game show ''[[Deal or No Deal (U.S. game show)|Deal or No Deal]]''.<ref name=\"Esquire\"/> She appeared in [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]'s series ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]'' as Junior Agent Amy Jessup in the first two episodes of its second season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/meghan-markle-joins-fringe-85750 |title=Meghan Markle joins 'Fringe' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=June 23, 2009 |accessdate=June 24, 2009 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629161102/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/meghan-markle-joins-fringe-85750 |archivedate=June 29, 2011}}</ref>\n\nMarkle had some difficulty getting roles early in her career. In 2015, she wrote: \"Being 'ethnically ambiguous', as I was pegged in the industry, meant I could audition for virtually any role&nbsp;... Sadly, it didn't matter: I wasn't black enough for the black roles and I wasn't white enough for the white ones, leaving me somewhere in the middle as the ethnic chameleon who couldn't book a job.\"<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/11/27/europe/meghan-markle-profile/index.html |title=Meghan Markle: Who is Prince Harry's bride-to-be? |author=Judith Vonberg |publisher=CNN |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127115929/http://www.cnn.com/2017/11/27/europe/meghan-markle-profile/index.html |archivedate=November 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nMarkle appeared in two 2010 films, ''[[Get Him to the Greek]]'' and ''[[Remember Me (2010 film)|Remember Me]]'', and one 2011 film, ''[[Horrible Bosses]]''.<ref name=\"thrlegalmind\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/meghan-markle-books-lead-role-27013 |title=Meghan Markle books lead role on 'Legal Mind' |first=James |last=Hibberd |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=August 24, 2010 |accessdate=November 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170123195551/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/meghan-markle-books-lead-role-27013 |archivedate=January 23, 2017}}</ref> She was paid $187,000 for her role in ''Remember Me'' and $171,429 for her role in the short film ''The Candidate''.<ref name=\"net worth\">{{cite web |last1=Dangremond |first1=Sam |title=Meghan Markle Net Worth 2017 |url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/money-and-power/a13085480/meghan-markle-net-worth/ |website=[[Town & Country (magazine)|Town & Country]] |accessdate=April 4, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202021206/https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/money-and-power/a13085480/meghan-markle-net-worth/ |archivedate=December 2, 2017 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Meghan Markle and Patrick J. Adams (Paley Center 'Suits').jpg|thumb|Markle with co-star [[Patrick J. Adams]] at a panel discussion of ''Suits'', [[Paley Center for Media]], 2013]]\nIn July 2011, Markle joined the cast of the [[USA Network]] show ''[[Suits (American TV series)|Suits]]''. Her character, [[Rachel Zane]], began as a [[paralegal]] and eventually became an attorney. She completed work on the seventh season in late 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/meghan-markle-suits-quit-royal-engagement-prince-harry-season-7-8-tv-show-a8077746.html |title=Meghan Markle to quit Suits after engagement to Prince Harry |date=November 27, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127111558/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/meghan-markle-suits-quit-royal-engagement-prince-harry-season-7-8-tv-show-a8077746.html |archivedate=November 27, 2017 |df=}}</ref> According to a critique in ''[[The Irish Times]]'', Markle \"actively re-positioned\" her character from ing\u00e9nue to \"the show's moral conscience\" and gave viewers the unique portrayal of a daughter whose African-American father is in a position to help her career and advance her \"desire to crack both racial and gender [[glass ceilings]]\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/tv-radio-web/meghan-markle-s-final-episode-of-suits-features-her-in-a-wedding-dress-1.3475148 |title=Meghan Markle's final episode of 'Suits' features her in a wedding dress |date=April 26, 2018 |work=The Irish Times |access-date=May 22, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> While working on ''Suits'', Markle lived for nine months each year in a rented house in the [[Seaton Village]] neighborhood of Toronto.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/12/12/meghan-markles-toronto-home-prince-harry-stayed-sale/ |title=Meghan Markle's Toronto home \u2013 where Prince Harry stayed \u2013 up for sale |work=The Telegraph |last=Horton |first=Helena |date=December 12, 2017|access-date=December 5, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Murphy BBC\"/> ''[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]'' magazine estimated that Markle was paid $50,000 per episode, amounting to an annual salary of about $450,000.<ref name=\"fortune\">{{cite web |title=Prince Harry and Meghan Markle: What's Their Net Worth? |work=Fortune |url=http://fortune.com/2017/11/27/prince-harry-meghan-markle-net-worth/ |date=April 4, 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180404123759/http://fortune.com/2017/11/27/prince-harry-meghan-markle-net-worth/ |archivedate=April 4, 2018 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMarkle began a relationship with actor and producer [[Trevor Engelson]] in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newsweek.com/who-meghan-markles-ex-husband-trevor-engelson-722843 |title=Who Is Meghan Markle's Ex-Husband, Trevor Engelson? |work=[[Newsweek]] |first=Tom |last=Porter |date=November 27, 2017 |accessdate=December 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171211015759/http://www.newsweek.com/who-meghan-markles-ex-husband-trevor-engelson-722843 |archivedate=December 11, 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://forward.com/schmooze/388553/how-meghan-markles-jewish-ex-husband-became-the-guy-who-lost-future-royal-b/ |title=How Meghan Markle's Jewish Ex-Husband Became The Guy Who Lost Future Royal Bride |work=Forward.com |date=November 19, 2017 }}</ref> They were married in [[Ocho Rios]], Jamaica, on September 10, 2011,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hitched-hatched-hired-240470 |title=Hitched, Hatched, Hired |date=September 27, 2011 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024230058/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hitched-hatched-hired-240470 |archivedate=October 24, 2012 |url-status=live |accessdate=February 2, 2013}}</ref> and concluded a [[no-fault divorce]] in August 2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/36-things-learnt-meghan-markle-past-year/ |title=36 things we've learnt about Meghan Markle in the past year |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=September 5, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818062326/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/36-things-learnt-meghan-markle-past-year/ |archivedate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> citing irreconcilable differences.<ref name=\"TCMMEX406182\">{{cite news |url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/tradition/a12655965/trevor-engelson-meghan-markle-ex-husband-facts/ |title=Meghan Markle's Ex-Husband Trevor Engelson Just Got Engaged |date=June 4, 2018 |work=Town & Country |accessdate=July 15, 2018}}</ref> Markle's subsequent relationship with celebrity chef and restaurateur [[Cory Vitiello]] lasted almost two years, ending in May 2016.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/31/prince-harry-met-new-girlfriend-while-she-was-still-dating-celeb/ |title=Prince Harry 'met new girlfriend while she was still dating celebrity chef' |last=Rayner |first=Gordon |date=October 31, 2016 |work=The Telegraph|access-date=July 16, 2018 |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Harry and Meghan on Christmas Day 2017 (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|Markle and Prince Harry attending church on Christmas Day, 2017]]\n\nIn June 2016, Markle began a relationship with [[Prince Harry]],<ref name=\"Cambridge\">{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/26/duke-cambridge-approved-prince-harrys-plea-trolls-leave-meghan/ |title=The Duke of Cambridge approved Prince Harry's plea to trolls to leave Meghan Markle alone |first=Gordon |last=Rayner |website=The Daily Telegraph |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912063947/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/26/duke-cambridge-approved-prince-harrys-plea-trolls-leave-meghan/ |archivedate=September 12, 2017 |url-status=live |access-date=September 5, 2017}}</ref> whom she had met on a blind date set up by a mutual friend.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/27/harry-meghan-blind-date-engagement-words/ |title=Prince Harry and Meghan Markle engaged: 'She didn't even let me finish!' Couple describe 'sweet, natural and very romantic' proposal |last=Furness |first=Hannah |date=November 27, 2017 |work=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=November 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127233239/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/27/harry-meghan-blind-date-engagement-words/|archive-date=November 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> At the time, he was fifth in [[line to the British throne]];<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/prince-harry-meghan-markle-royal-wedding-marriage-engaged-1.4417681 |title=Prince Harry, Meghan Markle to finally tie the knot |publisher=CBC News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127144359/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/prince-harry-meghan-markle-royal-wedding-marriage-engaged-1.4417681 |archivedate=November 27, 2017}}</ref> his grandmother is [[Elizabeth II]], queen of the United Kingdom and 15 other [[Commonwealth realms]], as well as [[head of the Commonwealth]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-commonwealth-harry/prince-harry-promises-to-listen-as-he-starts-new-commonwealth-job-idUSKBN1HM10N |title=Prince Harry promises to listen as he starts new Commonwealth job |publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=April 18, 2018 |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |first=William |last=James}}</ref> In November, the [[British royal family]]'s communications secretary released an official statement that addressed sexism, racism, and defamatory stories directed toward Markle.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.royal.uk/statement-communications-secretary-prince-harry |title=A Statement by the Communications Secretary to Prince Harry |last=Vallance |first=Adam |date=November 8, 2016 |publisher=The Royal Family |access-date=September 26, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927052849/https://www.royal.uk/statement-communications-secretary-prince-harry |archivedate=September 27, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Guardian on smear\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/nov/08/prince-harry-lambasts-press-over-meghan-markle-coverage |title=Prince Harry attacks press over 'wave of abuse' of girlfriend Meghan Markle |work=The Guardian |first1=Robert |last1=Booth |author2=Lisa O'Carroll |date=November 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907173906/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/nov/08/prince-harry-lambasts-press-over-meghan-markle-coverage |archivedate=September 7, 2017}}</ref> In September 2017, Markle and Prince Harry appeared together in public for the first time at an official royal engagement at the [[Invictus Games]] in [[Toronto]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-41376139 |title=Meghan Markle attends Invictus Games |date=September 24, 2017 |work=BBC News Online |access-date=September 26, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927085407/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-41376139 |archivedate=September 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/prince-harry-meghan-markle-make-official-public-appearance/story?id=50007178 |title=Prince Harry, Meghan Markle make first official public appearance |date=September 26, 2017 |publisher=ABC News|access-date=September 26, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925041954/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/prince-harry-meghan-markle-make-official-public-appearance/story?id=50007178 |archivedate=September 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Marriage to Prince Harry===\n{{further|Wedding of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle|Wedding dress of Meghan Markle}}\nMarkle's engagement to Prince Harry was announced on November 27, 2017, by [[Clarence House]] and [[Kensington Palace]].<ref name=\"Cambridge\"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bourke |first1=Latika |title=Royal wedding: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle announce engagement |url=http://www.theage.com.au/world/royal-wedding-prince-harry-and-meghan-markle-announce-engagement-20171127-gztxks.html |accessdate=November 27, 2017 |work=[[The Age]] |date=November 27, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127200809/http://www.theage.com.au/world/royal-wedding-prince-harry-and-meghan-markle-announce-engagement-20171127-gztxks.html |archivedate=November 27, 2017}}</ref> The announcement prompted generally positive comments about the possible social significance of a mixed-race member of the royal family.<ref name=race>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/meghan-markle-has-already-changed-way-think-race/ |title=Meghan Markle has already changed the way we think about race |first=Sunder |last=Katwala |date=May 25, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref> Markle announced that she would retire from acting,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Falzone |first1=Diana |title=Meghan Markle will quit acting following engagement to Prince Harry |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/11/27/meghan-markle-will-quit-acting-following-engagement-to-prince-harry-royal-experts-say.html |accessdate=November 27, 2017 |publisher=[[Fox News]] Channel |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127170734/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/11/27/meghan-markle-will-quit-acting-following-engagement-to-prince-harry-royal-experts-say.html |archivedate=November 27, 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-44168082 |title=Prince Charles to walk Meghan down the aisle |date=May 18, 2018 |publisher= |via=www.bbc.com}}</ref> and began the process of becoming a [[British citizen]].<ref name=\"citizen\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-42169602 |title=How will Meghan Markle become a British citizen? |publisher=BBC News |first= |last= |date=December 1, 2017 |accessdate=July 12, 2018}}</ref> In preparation for the [[wedding of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle|wedding]], the [[Archbishop of Canterbury]], [[Justin Welby]], [[baptized]] Markle and [[confirmed]] her into the [[Church of England]] on March 6, 2018.<ref name=\"baptism\">{{cite web |title=Meghan Markle 'baptised by Archbishop of Canterbury ahead of wedding to Prince Harry' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/03/08/meghan-markle-baptised-archbishop-canterbury-ahead-wedding-prince/ |work=The Daily Telegraph |first=Stephen |last=Walter |date=March 8, 2018 |accessdate=March 9, 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180309204847/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/03/08/meghan-markle-baptised-archbishop-canterbury-ahead-wedding-prince/ |archivedate=March 9, 2018}}</ref> The private ceremony, performed with water from the [[River Jordan]], took place in the Chapel Royal at [[St James's Palace]].<ref name=\"baptism\" /> The [[Wedding of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle|marriage ceremony]] was held on May 19 at [[St George's Chapel, Windsor Castle]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/18/st-georges-chapel-inside-windsor-castle-venue-tomorrows-royal/ |title=St George's Chapel: Inside the Windsor Castle venue for tomorrow's royal wedding |last=Vickers |first=Hugo |date=May 18, 2018 |work=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=May 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter the wedding, the Duke and Duchess originally lived at [[Nottingham Cottage]] in London, on the grounds of Kensington Palace.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/20/nottingham-cottage-kensington-home-meghan-harry-will-live-married/ |title=Nottingham Cottage: The Kensington home where Meghan and Harry live as a married couple |newspaper=The Telegraph |first=Victoria |last=Ward |date=May 22, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018}}</ref> The couple later moved to the more than two-centuries-old [[Frogmore Cottage]] in the [[Home Park, Windsor|Home Park]] of [[Windsor Castle]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/child-coming-it-s-suburbs-prince-harry-meghan-markle-n939631 |title=With child coming, it's off to the country for Prince Harry and Meghan Markle |publisher=NBC News |date=November 24, 2018 |accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/prince-harry-and-meghan-are-moving-to-the-suburbs-frogmore-cottage-2018-11-24/ |title=Prince Harry and Meghan are moving to the suburbs |publisher=CBS News |date=November 24, 2018 |accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> The [[Crown Estate]] refurbished the cottage at a cost of \u00a32.4 million, paid out of the [[Sovereign Grant]], with the couple picking up expenses beyond restoration and ordinary maintenance.<ref>{{cite web |title=Harry and Meghan taxpayer-funded renovations cost \u00a32.4m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-48746609 |website=[[BBC News]] |accessdate=June 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u00a32.4m bill for renovation of Meghan and Harry's house, Frogmore Cottage |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/2-4m-bill-for-renovation-of-meghan-and-harry-s-house-frogmore-cottage-mxwg6wbdj |work=[[The Times]]|location=London|accessdate=June 25, 2019}}</ref> Their office was moved to [[Buckingham Palace]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://people.com/royals/meghan-markle-prince-harry-split-households-kate-middleton-prince-william/ |title=Meghan Markle and Prince Harry Have Split Royal Households from Kate Middleton and Prince William |magazine=People |first=Erin |last=Hill |date=March 14, 2019 |accessdate=March 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402132823/https://people.com/royals/meghan-markle-prince-harry-split-households-kate-middleton-prince-william/ |archive-date=April 2, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On May 6, 2019, the Duchess gave birth to [[Archie Mountbatten-Windsor]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Barry |first1=Ellen |last2=Karasz |first2=Palko |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/06/world/europe/meghan-markle-baby-boy.html |title=Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, gives birth to a boy |work=The New York Times |date=May 6, 2019|access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref> who is seventh in line to the throne.<ref name=\"pregnancy\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-45861683 |title=Meghan and Harry: Duchess of Sussex expecting a baby |publisher=BBC News |last= |date=October 15, 2018 |accessdate=October 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Fashion and style==\n{{anchor|The Tig}}In 2014, Markle founded the lifestyle website ''The Tig'', where she wrote about food, fashion, beauty and travel, and profiled inspirational women.<ref name=\"actresstoduchess\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-37908788 |title=Meghan: From actress to duchess |publisher=BBC |date=October 15, 2018 |accessdate=January 6, 2018 |first= |last=}}</ref> As the website grew, Markle brought in experts such as dieticians, make-up artists, and fitness and yoga instructors. The website's audience consisted primarily of the fans of Markle and ''Suits''. Markle reinforced ''The Tig''{{'}}s messages of [[self-love]], positivity, and spirituality on social media, reaching 3 million followers on [[Instagram]], 800,000 on [[Facebook]], and 350,000 on [[Twitter]]. She closed ''The Tig'' in April 2017, taking all of its articles offline, and deleted her social media accounts in January 2018.<ref name=\"wellnessguru\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-43241866 |title=Meghan Markle: The wellness guru she could have been |publisher=BBC |date=March 24, 2018 |accessdate=January 6, 2018 |first=Mary-Ann |last=Russon}}</ref> It was estimated that, as a lifestyle blogger, Markle earned about $80,000 annually from endorsements and sponsorships.<ref name=\"net worth\" />\n\nAs editor-in-chief of ''The Tig'', Markle became known for her fashion sense.<ref name=\"Murphy BBC\"/> She released two fashion collections with Canadian clothing company [[Reitmans]] in 2015 and 2016.<ref name=\"wellnessguru\"/> The lines were based on her personal style and that of her ''Suits'' character, described as \"aspirational girl next door\", and quickly sold out.<ref name=\"Murphy BBC\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-41768867 |title=Meghan's pageboys and Toronto 'royalty' |last=Murphy |first=Jessica |date=May 18, 2018 |website=BBC News |language=en-GB |access-date=May 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Meghan Markle in 2013 New York Fashion Week (34567271204).jpg|thumb|left|Markle at the [[New York Fashion Week]] in 2013]]\nMarkle has cited [[Emmanuelle Alt]] as her style inspiration.<ref name=Vogue-Style>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/meghan-markle-style-file |title=The Duchess Of Sussex: Style File |work=British Vogue |first=Orla |last=Pentelow |date=June 19, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Glam-Interview\">{{cite web |url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/gallery/meghan-markle-interview-about-suits-the-outnet-and-her-love-of-clothes |title=Meghan Markle chats to GLAMOUR about VB dresses, her personal style & her fashion cringe moments |work=Glamour UK |first=Leanne |last=Bayley |date=May 22, 2017 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'', the Duchess said that she favored \"that French way of styling, where if your outfit is pulled together, then something's got to be dishevelled\u2014your hair, your make-up\".<ref name=Vogue-Style/> In her youth, Markle's \"sensibility had always been relaxed California girl style\" consisting of jeans, cut-offs and flip-flops.<ref name=\"Glam-Interview\"/> She usually prefers \"streamlined dresses\" with \"neutral colors\" and [[bateau neckline]]s,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/meghan-markle-duchess-of-sussex-brandon-maxwell-commonwealth-youth-challenge |title=The Duchess Of Sussex Breaks Away From Her Uniform Style In Brandon Maxwell |work=British Vogue |first=Edward |last=Barsamian |date=July 6, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/meghan-markle-cant-stop-wearing-the-same-style-of-dress_us_5b3e629ae4b07b827cbe8f88 |title=Meghan Markle Can't Stop Wearing The Same Style Of Dress |work=HuffPost |first=Carly |last=Ledbetter |date=July 5, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2018}}</ref> and likes \"monochromatic and tonal dressing\".<ref name=\"Glam-Interview\"/> She has worn outfits and ensembles by a wide variety of fashion designers.<ref name=Vogue-Style/>\n\nIn December 2017, Markle caused a surge in interest in Scottish retailer [[Strathberry]] after carrying one of their handbags to a public event shortly after her engagement.<ref name=\"Tel-Bag\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/12/01/scottish-luxury-handbag-company-gets-big-break-sending-sample/ |title=Scottish family handbag firm feels the 'Meghan effect' as Strathberry orders soar |last=Ward |first=Victoria |date=December 1, 2017 |work=The Telegraph|access-date=February 9, 2018 |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT-Influence\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/25/style/meghan-markle-influencer-suits-wedding.html |title=Meghan Markle: The Biggest Influencer of All? |newspaper=The New York Times |first=Vanessa |last=Friedman |date=April 25, 2018 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> This was reported as an indication that her fashion choices would produce her own version of the [[Kate effect]].<ref name=\"Tel-Bag\"/><ref name=\"Vogue-Effect\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/meghan-markle-fashion |title=The Meaning Of Meghan |work=British Vogue |first=Afua |last=Hirsch |first2=Claudia |last2=Croft |date=May 18, 2018 |accessdate=May 31, 2018}}</ref> After Markle and Prince Harry's first appearance as a couple, brands Mackage, [[Birks Group|Birks]], R&R Jewelers, Crown Jewelers and [[Everlane]] noted an upswing in their website hits and sales.<ref>{{cite news |title=How to Dress Meghan Markle (Hint: You Probably Can't) |url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/articles/intelligence/the-challenges-of-dressing-meghan-markle |accessdate=May 24, 2018 |work=The Business of Fashion |date=May 16, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/05/25/meghan-markle-makes-gold-sales-sparkle.html |title=Meghan Markle makes gold sales sparkle |publisher=CNBC |date=May 25, 2018 |accessdate=May 31, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT-Influence\"/> It has been speculated that Markle's effect would be greater, as she has a strong appeal in America.<ref name=\"Vogue-Effect\"/> She caused a boost in the sales of yellow gold in the first quarter of 2018 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-global-precious-royals/meghan-markle-makes-gold-sales-sparkle-idUSKCN1IQ0FU|title=Meghan Markle makes gold sales sparkle|publisher=Reuters|first=Renita D.|last=Young|date=May 25, 2018|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, ''[[Tatler]]'' named the Duchess on its list of Britain's best dressed people, praising her for redefining \"modern royal style with every subsequent appearance\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-45038649 |title=Royal Family lead Tatler's 2018 best-dressed Brits list |publisher=BBC |date=August 2, 2018 |accessdate=October 18, 2018}}</ref> Following the announcement of her pregnancy, the Duchess appeared in a Karen Gee dress that resulted in the breakdown of the designer's website.<ref name=\"Pregnancy-Fashion\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-45888396 |title=Meghan's maternity and the fashion brands hoping to strike gold |publisher=BBC |first=Becky |last=Morton |date=October 17, 2018 |accessdate=October 18, 2018}}</ref> She was ranked one of the best dressed women in 2018 by fashion website [[Net-a-Porter]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Best Dressed 2018 |url=https://www.net-a-porter.com/gb/en/porter/article-f0fe0982c9ceac88/cover-stories/cover-stories/best-dressed-2018 |website=Net a Porter}}</ref> and was nominated for the [[2018 Teen Choice Awards]] in the category Choice Style Icon.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/943773/teen-choice-awards-2018-avengers-infinity-war-black-panther-and-riverdale-among-top-nominees |title=Teen Choice Awards 2018: ''Avengers: Infinity War'', ''Black Panther'' and ''Riverdale'' Among Top Nominees |last=Cohen |first=Jess |work=[[E! News]] |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 13, 2018}}</ref> In 2019, British brand [[Reiss (brand)|Reiss]] reported a growth in profits, after the Duchess was seen wearing a mini-dress by them on International Women's Day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/fashion/brands/duchess-sussex-effect-reiss-got-mojo-back/|title=The Duchess of Sussex effect: how Reiss got its mojo back|publisher=The Telegraph|first=Tamara|last=Abraham|date=August 23, 2019|accessdate=August 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Public role==\n[[File:Prince Harry and Ms. Markle visit Belfast\u2019s Crown Liquor Saloon (40263263684).jpg|thumb|left|Markle greeting the public in Belfast, March 2018]]\nMarkle was politically vocal before joining the British royal family. She backed [[Hillary Clinton]] during the [[2016 United States presidential election]] and described Clinton's opponent, [[Donald Trump]], as \"[[misogynistic]]\" and \"divisive\". The same year, when the [[referendum on the United Kingdom's membership of the European Union]] resulted in 51.9% of voters being in favor of [[Brexit]], Markle expressed her disappointment on Instagram and posted a placard saying: \"If [[EU]] leave me now, you take away the biggest part of me.\"<ref name=\"Booth\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/nov/29/meghan-markle-royal-protocol-donald-trump-brexit |title=Meghan Markle's activism to be held in check by royal protocol |work=The Guardian |first=Robert |last=Booth |date=November 30, 2017 |accessdate=January 6, 2019}}</ref> This, as well as her recommendation of [[Noam Chomsky]]'s book ''[[Who Rules the World?]]'', led Emine Saner of ''[[The Guardian]]'' to write that Markle would become \"the most leftwing member of the royal family\".<ref name=\"Saner\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/dec/01/not-your-average-royal-what-we-know-so-far-about-meghan-markle |title=Not your average royal: what we know so far about Meghan Markle |work=The Guardian |first=Emine |last=Saner |date=December 1, 2017 |accessdate=January 6, 2019}}</ref> Members of the royal family are politically neutral by convention, and [[Dickie Arbiter]], former press secretary to Prince Charles, expects the Duchess to follow suit.<ref name=\"Booth\"/> Historian [[Robert Lacey]] said she was the most \"feisty and spiky\" person to marry into the royal family since her grandfather-in-law [[Prince Philip]].<ref name=\"Booth\"/>\n\nAfter the engagement, Markle's first official public appearance with Prince Harry was at a [[World AIDS Day]] walkabout in [[Nottingham]] on December 1, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/dec/01/meghan-markle-begins-royal-induction-with-nottingham-walkabout-prince-harry |title=Meghan Markle begins royal induction with Nottingham walkabout |work=The Guardian |first=Caroline |last=Davies |date=December 1, 2017 |accessdate=December 4, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203214532/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/dec/01/meghan-markle-begins-royal-induction-with-nottingham-walkabout-prince-harry |archivedate=December 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-42181189 |title=Prince Harry and Meghan Markle wow Nottingham crowds on first joint visit |publisher=BBC |date=December 1, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203053624/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-42181189 |archivedate=December 3, 2017 |df=}}</ref> The [[Commonwealth Day]] service at [[Westminster Abbey]] on March 12 was the first royal event she attended with the Queen.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/meghan-markle-joins-queen-for-first-time-at-official-royal-event-pg86s52jc |title=Meghan Markle joins Queen for first time at official royal event |work=The Times|location=London |date=March 12, 2018 |accessdate=March 12, 2018}}</ref> The couple made their first visit to Northern Ireland on March 23.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/03/23/prince-harry-meghan-markle-northern-ireland-couples-rapturous/ |title=Prince Harry and Meghan Markle in Northern Ireland: Couple's rapturous welcome on unannounced visit |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=March 23, 2018 |accessdate=March 23, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180323130822/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/03/23/prince-harry-meghan-markle-northern-ireland-couples-rapturous/ |archivedate=March 23, 2018}}</ref> Markle carried out a total of 26 public engagements prior to the wedding.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/19/royal-wedding-facts-figures-many-people-invited-cost-windsor/ |title=Royal wedding facts and figures: From how many people are invited, to the cost of Windsor parking |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |date=May 21, 2018 |accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ceremony of Welcome for TRH The Duke and Duchess of Sussex (14).jpg|right|thumb|The Duke and Duchess of Sussex welcomed to New Zealand, October 2018]]\nThe Duchess's first official engagement after the wedding came on May 22 when she and her husband celebrated the charity work of his father, [[Prince Charles]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/22/prince-harry-meghan-markle-make-first-appearance-married-couple/ |title=Duke and Duchess of Sussex make first appearance as a married couple at Prince Charles' 70th birthday party |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |first=Hannah |last=Furness |date=May 22, 2018 |accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref> Her first trip abroad at the request of the British government was to [[Dublin]], Ireland, in July 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.ie/style/celebrity/celebrity-news/britains-prince-harry-and-meghan-markle-set-for-first-trip-abroad-as-newlyweds-with-dublin-tour-37026481.html |title=Britain's Prince Harry and Meghan Markle set for first trip abroad as newlyweds with Dublin tour |work=Independent.ie |date=June 19, 2018 |access-date=June 19, 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/life-and-style/people/prince-harry-and-meghan-markle-to-visit-dublin-1.3536037 |title=Prince Harry and Meghan Markle to visit Dublin |work=The Irish Times |date=June 19, 2018 |access-date=June 19, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> The Duchess takes part in her husband's work as [[youth ambassador]] to the Commonwealth, which includes overseas tours.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/04/16/prince-harry-revealsmeghan-markle-will-take-commonwealth-role/ |title=Prince Harry reveals Meghan Markle will take on Commonwealth role |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |first=Hannah |last=Furness |date=April 16, 2018 |accessdate=December 19, 2018}}</ref> The first such trip was to Australia, Fiji, Tonga and New Zealand in October 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/in-pictures-45939855 |title=Royal tour: Harry and Meghan's overseas trip so far |publisher=BBC |date=October 31, 2018 |accessdate=December 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Lyons\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/oct/19/prince-harry-meghan-australia-duke-duchess-sussex |title=Bearing a baby and banana bread, Harry and Meghan enchant Australia |newspaper=The Guardian |first=Kate |last=Lyons |date=October 19, 2018 |accessdate=December 19, 2018}}</ref> Despite public debate on the future of the [[monarchy in Australia]], the couple were greeted by crowds in [[Sydney]], and the announcement of the Duchess's pregnancy hours after their arrival was received enthusiastically by the public and media.<ref name=\"Lyons\"/><ref name=\"Furness\">{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/royal-family/2018/10/15/prince-harry-meghan-markle-turn-royal-family-advice-tour/ |title=Duchess of Sussex says 'we're ready and excited to join the club' after pregnancy announcement |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |first=Hannah |last=Furness |date=October 16, 2018 |accessdate=December 19, 2018}}</ref> During their visit to [[Morocco]] in February 2019, the Duke and Duchess focused on projects centered on \"women's empowerment, girls' education, inclusivity and encouragement of social entrepreneurship\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/royals/meghan-markle-prince-harry-morocco-royal-tour/ |title=Meghan Markle and Prince Harry Arrive Hand-in-Hand in Morocco for Last Royal Tour Before Baby |work=People |first=Simon |last=Perry |first2=Erin |last2=Hill |date=February 23, 2019 |accessdate=February 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine included Markle on its list of the [[100 Most Influential People in the World]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/04/19/ruth-davidson-named-times-100-influential-people-2018/|title=Ruth Davidson named in Time's 100 most influential people of 2018|last=Furness |first=Hannah |date=December 10, 2018 |work=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=January 8, 2020}}</ref> and placed her on its shortlist for [[Time Person of the Year|Person of the Year]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/royal-family/2018/12/10/duchess-sussex-shortlisted-time-magazines-person-year-along/|title=Duchess of Sussex shortlisted for Time magazine's 'Person of the Year' \u2013 along with Trump and Putin|last=Cramb|first=Auslan|date=April 19, 2018 |work=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=January 8, 2020}}</ref> She was also chosen as one of the most influential women in the United Kingdom by [[British Vogue|British ''Vogue'']] magazine.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/vogue-25-the-women-shaping-2018 |title=The Vogue 25: Meet The Women Shaping 2018 |date=May 31, 2018 |work=British Vogue |accessdate=May 31, 2018}}</ref> As part of setting up their separate office or 'court' in 2019, the Duke and Duchess created an [[Instagram]] social media account, which broke the record for fastest account to reach 1 million followers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/2019/04/02/prince-harry-meghan-instagram-debut-royals-launch-new-separate-account/3340999002/ |title=Harry and Meghan's new Instagram account is a record-breaking hit with millions |website=USA TODAY |language=en|access-date=April 20, 2019}}</ref> In August 2019, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were criticized by environmental campaigners for using private jets regularly when taking their personal trips abroad, which would leave more [[carbon footprint]] per person compared to commercial planes. The criticism was in line with the reactions the royal family faced in June 2019, after it was revealed that they \"had doubled [their] carbon footprint from business travel\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/harry-used-private-jet-twice-in-a-week-after-climate-talks-pwv57fnj3 |title=Prince Harry used private jet twice in a week after climate talks |work=The Times|location=London|first=Ben |last=Webster |date=August 19, 2019 |accessdate=August 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/19/uk/harry-meghan-private-jets-gbr-intl/index.html |title=Harry and Meghan branded hypocrites for using private jets |publisher=CNN |first=Bianca |last=Britton |date=August 20, 2019 |accessdate=August 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Sussexes' discontent with their public roles and media scrutiny grew in 2019.<ref name=\"Kevin\">{{cite news|first1=Kevin|last1=Rawlinson|first2=Caroline|last2=Davies|title=Prince Harry and Meghan to step back from royal family|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/08/prince-harry-and-meghan-say-they-are-stepping-back-from-royal-family|website=The Daily Telegraph|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> In May 2019, [[Splash News]] issued a formal apology to Harry and his wife for sending photographers to their [[Cotswolds]] residence, which put their privacy at risk. The agency also agreed to pay a \"substantial\" sum of damages and legal costs associated with the case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-48296202|title=Prince Harry accepts damages over Splash News Agency photos|publisher=BBC|date=16 May 2019|accessdate=16 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/16/europe/prince-harry-meghan-helicopter-pictures-gbr-intl-scli/index.html|title=Prince Harry accepts 'substantial' damages after helicopter photos forced royal couple from their home|publisher=CNN|first=Rob|last=Picheta|first2=Max|last2=Foster|date=16 May 2019|accessdate=16 May 2019}}</ref> At the end of their tour of [[Southern Africa]]n countries in September\u2013October 2019, it emerged that the Duchess was suing ''[[The Mail on Sunday]]'' over the publication of a letter she had sent to her father.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-49904428|title=Meghan and Harry's tour ends as Mail on Sunday vows to defend itself in court|publisher=BBC|date=October 2, 2019 |accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Prince Harry condemns 'ruthless campaign' against Meghan, saying he lost his mother to 'powerful forces' and fears history repeating |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/royal-family/2019/10/01/duchess-sussex-sue-mail-sunday-publication-private-letter/ |website=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref> Seventy-two female [[British MP]]s sent a public letter of support to the Duchess, condemning the \"outdated, colonial undertones\" in the press.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/10/29/world/female-mps-meghan-press-coverage-scli-intl/index.html|title=British female MPs sign open letter to Meghan condemning 'outdated, colonial undertones' of press coverage|publisher=CNN|first=Rory|last=Sullivan|date=October 29, 2019|accessdate=October 29, 2019}}</ref> In January 2020, the Duke and Duchess announced that [[Megxit|they were stepping back]] from their role as senior members of the royal family, and that they would balance their time between the United Kingdom and North America.<ref>{{cite web |title=Duke and Duchess of Sussex step back from senior royal duties. Read their full statement |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/08/uk/harry-meghan-step-back-from-royal-family-full-statement-gbr-intl/index.html | publisher = CNN | date=January 8, 2020 | accessdate = January 8, 2020}}</ref> The couple also said that they would seek financial independence while continuing to support their charities and the Queen.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/prince-harry-and-meghan-to-step-back-as-senior-royals-and-split-time-between-britain-and-north-america/2020/01/08/564f3e32-3249-11ea-971b-43bec3ff9860_story.html|title=Prince Harry and Meghan to \u2018step back\u2019 as senior royals and split time between Britain and North America|newspaper=The Washington Post|first=William|last=Booth|first2=Karla|last2=Adam|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> In the same month, the couple's lawyers issued a legal warning to the press after paparazzi photographs were published in the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/jan/21/harry-and-meghan-legal-warning-latest-twist-in-royal-paparazzi-feud|title=Harry and Meghan legal warning latest twist in royal paparazzi feud|newspaper=The Guardian|first=Ben|last=Quinn|date=21 January 2020|accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref> The Duchess's final solo engagement as a senior royal was a visit to [[Robert Clack School]] in [[Dagenham]] ahead of [[International Women's Day]]. She and her husband will officially step down on March 31.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/09/uk/student-letter-to-prince-harry-intl-scli-gbr/index.html|title=High school student apologizes to Prince Harry for 'cuddling' Meghan|publisher = CNN | date=March 9, 2020 | accessdate = March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charity work==\n[[File:Brian Urlacher, Meghan Markle and Doug Fister, 2014.jpg|thumb|right|Markle and sportsmen [[Brian Urlacher]] and [[Doug Fister]] address the audience during a [[USO]] show at [[Naval Station Rota, Spain]], December 6, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dvidshub.net/image/1690965/2014-cjcs-holiday-uso-tour |title=2014 CJCS Holiday USO Tour |date=December 6, 2014 |publisher=Defense Visual Information Distribution Service|access-date=November 28, 2018}}</ref>]]\nMarkle was a counselor for international charity [[One Young World]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ottawa.ctvnews.ca/justin-trudeau-welcomes-emma-watson-bob-geldoff-and-other-star-activists-to-parliament-hill-1.3093617 |title=Justin Trudeau welcomes Emma Watson, Bob Geldoff, and other star activists to Parliament Hill |website=Ottawa.ctvnews.ca |accessdate=May 23, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509064321/http://ottawa.ctvnews.ca/justin-trudeau-welcomes-emma-watson-bob-geldoff-and-other-star-activists-to-parliament-hill-1.3093617 |archivedate=May 9, 2017}}</ref> At the 2014 summit in Dublin, she spoke on the topics of [[gender equality]] and [[modern-day slavery]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Sarah |last=Stack |url=https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/one-young-world/meghan-markle-i-had-to-refuse-being-filmed-in-just-a-towel-every-day-30672579.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141212031024/https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/one-young-world/meghan-markle-i-had-to-refuse-being-filmed-in-just-a-towel-every-day-30672579.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2014-12-12 |title=Meghan Markle: I had to refuse being filmed in just a towel every day |work=The Irish Independent |publisher=[[Independent News & Media]] |location=Dublin, Ireland}}</ref> Also in 2014, she toured Afghanistan and Spain with the [[United Service Organizations]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.uso.org/stories/1547-the-year-in-uso-entertainment |title=The Year in USO Entertainment |work=United Service Organizations|access-date=December 3, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170201123251/https://www.uso.org/stories/1547-the-year-in-uso-entertainment |archivedate=February 1, 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/897645/a-look-back-at-meghan-markle-s-pre-royal-life#photo-867837 |title=A Look Back at Meghan Markle's Pre-Royal Life |work=E!|access-date=December 3, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202022412/http://www.eonline.com/news/897645/a-look-back-at-meghan-markle-s-pre-royal-life#photo-867837 |archivedate=December 2, 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/meghan-markle-prince-harry-girlfriend |title=Meet Meghan Markle: Prince Harry's Feminist, Philanthropist, Actress Girlfriend |work=Vogue |first=Michelle |last=Ruiz|access-date=December 3, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915160757/https://www.vogue.com/article/meghan-markle-prince-harry-girlfriend |archivedate=September 15, 2017 |df=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Markle became a global ambassador for [[World Vision Canada]], traveling to Rwanda for the Clean Water Campaign.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/meghan-markle-who-is-she-prince-harry-rumours-suits-actress-campaign-work-a7389571.html |title=Who is Meghan Markle: The 'Suits' actress, humanitarian, activist and gender equality campaigner |last=Blair |first=Olivia |date=October 31, 2016 |work=The Independent|access-date=September 15, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915160726/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/meghan-markle-who-is-she-prince-harry-rumours-suits-actress-campaign-work-a7389571.html |archivedate=September 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Watkins |first1=Janelle |title=Meghan Markle 'Suits' Up for Success |url=http://www.ebony.com/entertainment-culture/meghan-markle-suits-interview |accessdate=June 29, 2016 |agency=Eabony |date=February 29, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160421041624/http://www.ebony.com/entertainment-culture/meghan-markle-suits-interview |archivedate=April 21, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/> In 2016, after a trip to India focused on raising awareness for [[women in India|women's issues]], she penned an op-ed for ''Time'' magazine concerning stigmatization of women in regard to [[menstrual health]].<ref name=\"About\">{{cite web |date=May 18, 2018 |title=The Duchess of Sussex |url=https://www.royal.uk/duchess-sussex |magazine=The Royal Family|access-date=May 18, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> She has also worked with the [[United Nations Entity for Gender Equality and the Empowerment of Women]] as an Advocate.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://strategyonline.ca/2015/08/07/un-women-turn-on-the-light/ |title=UN Women turn on the light |first=Harmeet |last=Singh |date=August 7, 2015 |accessdate=November 28, 2016 |work=Strategy Online |publisher=Brunico Communications Ltd. |archivedate=August 17, 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150817060730/http://strategyonline.ca/2015/08/07/un-women-turn-on-the-light/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The Duchess is a vocal [[feminist]] and intends to use her role as a member of the royal family to continue supporting [[women's rights]] and [[social justice]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/20/meghan-markle-given-palaces-blessing-fight-feminism-takes-place/ |title=Meghan Markle to fight for feminism: New Duchess of Sussex given palace blessing to champion women's rights |last=Furness |first=Hannah |date=May 21, 2018 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=July 12, 2018}}</ref> In 2017, Markle joined Prince Harry in teaming up with the charity Elephants Without Borders to assist with the conservation efforts taking place in [[Botswana]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/royals/meghan-markle-prince-harry-new-photos-2017-botswana-trip-world-elephant-day/ |title=Meghan Markle and Prince Harry Share Never-Before-Seen Photos with Elephants from 2017 Botswana Trip |magazine=People |first=Stephanie |last=Petit |date=August 12, 2019 |accessdate=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMarkle became interested in the Hubb Community Kitchen, run by the survivors of [[Grenfell Tower fire]], in January 2018. She visited the kitchen regularly throughout 2018, and suggested that the displaced women publish a cookbook to obtain funding for it.<ref name=\"Guardian-book\">{{cite web |title=Meghan launches Grenfell recipe book in first project as Duchess of Sussex |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/sep/17/grenfell-tower-recipe-book-first-solo-project-for-meghan-markle-duchess-of-sussex |date=September 17, 2018 |first=Caroline |last=Davies |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190112021907/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/sep/17/grenfell-tower-recipe-book-first-solo-project-for-meghan-markle-duchess-of-sussex |archivedate=January 12, 2019|access-date = |url-status=live |df=mdy-all}}</ref> ''Together: Our Community Cookbook'', her first charity project as Duchess of Sussex, was announced in September.<ref name=\"CNN-book\">{{cite web |title=Meghan cooks for Grenfell: Duchess announces support for charity cookbook |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/17/uk/meghan-markle-grenfell-intl/index.html |date=September 17, 2018 |first=Eliza |last=Mackintosh |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190101202238/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/17/uk/meghan-markle-grenfell-intl/index.html |archivedate=January 1, 2019|access-date = January 1, 2019|url-status=live |df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, she attended the first annual forum of [[The Royal Foundation]];<ref>{{cite news |url=http://time.com/5179035/meghan-markle-prince-harry-prince-william-kate-middleton-royal-foundation-forum/ |title=Meghan Markle Shines at First Royal Engagement With Prince Harry, Prince William and Kate Middleton |work=Time |date=February 28, 2018 |access-date=March 9, 2018 |first=Megan |last=McCluskey |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180313104402/http://time.com/5179035/meghan-markle-prince-harry-prince-william-kate-middleton-royal-foundation-forum/ |archivedate=March 13, 2018}}</ref> she became the foundation's fourth patron, alongside Prince Harry, his brother [[Prince William]], and sister-in-law [[Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge|Catherine]], after her marriage into the royal family.<ref>{{cite web |title=Britain's royal 'Fab Four' attend first official event together |publisher=Reuters |url=https://ca.reuters.com/article/topNews/idCAKCN1GC1OJ-OCATP |first=Michael |last=Holden |date=February 28, 2018 |accessdate=March 9, 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180228202050/https://ca.reuters.com/article/topNews/idCAKCN1GC1OJ-OCATP |archivedate=February 28, 2018}}</ref> In June 2019, it was announced that the Duke and Duchess of Sussex would split from the charity and establish their own charity foundation by the end of 2019. However, the couples will reportedly collaborate on mutual projects, such as the mental health initiative Heads Together.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/20/uk/sussex-cambridge-royal-foundation-split-intl/index.html |title=Meghan and Harry split from joint charity with William and Kate |publisher=CNN |first=Max |last=Foster |first2=Bianca |last2=Britton |date=June 20, 2019 |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/royal-family/2019/06/20/royal-charity-splits-duke-duchess-sussex-leave-royal-foundation/ |title=Royal charity split: Duke and Duchess of Sussex to leave Royal Foundation |publisher=The Daily Telegraph |first=Hannah |last=Furness |date=June 20, 2019 |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> In July 2019, Harry and Meghan's new charity was registered in England and Wales under the title \"Sussex Royal The Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Sussex\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/celebrities/news/a28443339/sussex-royal-foundation/ |title=The Duke and Duchess of Sussex have named their royal foundation |publisher=Harper's Bazaar |date=July 19, 2019 |accessdate=July 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nHer patronage of London's [[Royal National Theatre|National Theatre]], the [[Association of Commonwealth Universities]], Smart Works, and [[The Mayhew Animal Home|Mayhew]] reflects her earlier interests in the arts, access to education, women's empowerment, and animal well-being, respectively.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-46822529 |title=Meghan made patron of National Theatre |publisher=BBC |date=January 10, 2019 |accessdate=January 10, 2019}}</ref> The Duchess was appointed the vice president of the Queen's Commonwealth Trust, which focuses on projects involving children and welfare of prisoners, in March 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/08/world/europe/meghan-markle-womens-day.html |title=Meghan Markle 'Moved the Dial' for British Royal Family in Women's Day Talk |newspaper=The New York Times |first=Ellen |last=Barry |date=March 8, 2019 |accessdate=March 8, 2019}}</ref>  In October 2019, the Duchess voiced a [[Public Health England]] announcement with other members of the royal family for the \"Every Mind Matters\" mental health program.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/prince-harry-meghan-markle-prince-william-kate-middleton-mental-health|title=Prince Harry, Meghan Markle reunite with Prince William, Kate Middleton for mental health PSA|publisher=Fox News|first=Stephanie|last=Nolasco|date=7 October 2019|accessdate=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, the Duchess became a contributor and guest editor for the September issue of [[British Vogue|British ''Vogue'']] and highlighted the works of 15 women from different areas, who were described as \"Forces for Change\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/meghan-duchess-of-sussex-guest-edits-british-vogue-revealing-women-she-admires/2019/07/29/b2fc4fbc-b1de-11e9-acc8-1d847bacca73_story.html |title=Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, guest-edits British Vogue, revealing women she admires |publisher=The Washington Post |first=Karla |last=Adam |date=July 29, 2019 |accessdate=July 30, 2019}}</ref> [[Edward Enninful]], editor-in-chief of the British ''Vogue'', later revealed that the issue had become the \"fastest-selling issue in the history of British ''Vogue''\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/meghan-british-vogue-guest-editor-intl-scli-gbr/index.html |title=Meghan wears a glittery party hat in behind-the-scenes footage of Vogue guest editorship |publisher=CNN |first=Amy |last=Woodyatt |date=February 14, 2020 |accessdate=February 14, 2020}}</ref> In the same issue, it was revealed that she had collaborated with a number of British fashion houses and stores to launch a capsule collection, called The Smart Set, in September 2019 to benefit the charity Smart Works, of which she is a patron. The collection sought to help \"unemployed and disadvantaged women\", through selling items \"on a one-for-one basis, meaning an item is donated for each item purchased\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a28554451/meghan-markle-collection-smart-works/ |title=Meghan Markle Is Launching a Collection of Workwear for a Good Cause |publisher=Harper's Bazaar |first=Erica |last=Gonzales |date=July 30, 2019 |accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref> Taking advantage of \"the Meghan effect\" (driving consumer purchases), in 10 days the collection provided a year's worth of clothes for the charity.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Foussianes |first=Chloe |date=2019-09-24 |title=Meghan Markle's Collection Has Already Provided Her Patronage with a Year's Worth of Clothing |url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/tradition/a29207665/meghan-markle-smart-works-collection-sales-results/ |magazine=Town and Country |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, it was announced that the Duchess would serve as the narrator of [[Disneynature]]'s documentary ''[[Elephant (2020 film)|Elephant]]''. The proceeds from the documentary, which will become available for streaming on [[Disney+]] on April 3, will be donated to Elephant Without Borders in order to help elephants in Botswana.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/meghan-duchess-sussex-narrate-movie-about-elephants-first-post-royal-n1169786|title=Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, to narrate movie about elephants in first post-royal project|publisher=NBC News|first=Henry|last=Austin|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Elephant-Doc\">{{cite news |last1=Vary |first1=Adam B. |title=Meghan Markle Narrating Disney Plus Nature Documentary \u2018Elephants\u2019 |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/meghan-markle-disney-plus-elephants-1203545835/ |accessdate=March 26, 2020 |work=Variety |date=March 26, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Titles, styles, and arms==\n[[File:Royal_Monogram_of_Meghan,_Duchess_of_Sussex.svg|thumb|100px|The Duchess of Sussex's [[monogram]]]]\nUpon her marriage to Prince Harry, Meghan Markle became a [[princess of the United Kingdom]] entitled to the style of [[Royal Highness]], as well as [[Duke of Sussex|Duchess of Sussex]], [[Countess of Dumbarton]] and [[Baroness Kilkeel]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Birth certificate shows baby Archie's birth place and Meghan's job |date=May 17, 2019 |work=Sky News |url=https://news.sky.com/story/baby-archie-was-born-in-a-private-hospital-birth-certificate-confirms-11722360 |accessdate=May 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Royal wedding: Harry and Meghan appointed Baron and Baroness of Kilkeel |date=May 19, 2018 |work=Belfast Telegraph |url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/royal-wedding-harry-and-meghan-appointed-baron-and-baroness-of-kilkeel-36923521.html |accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Fitzmaurice |first=Rosie |date=May 19, 2018 |title=Meghan Markle is officially a Duchess&nbsp;\u2014 here's her new title |work=Business Insider |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/meghan-markle-will-become-a-duchess-2018-5 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524202847/https://www.businessinsider.de/meghan-markle-will-become-a-duchess-2018-5?r=US&IR=T |archivedate=May 24, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> She is styled as \"Her Royal Highness The Duchess of Sussex\",<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.royal.uk/prince-harry-and-ms-meghan-markle-announcement-titles |title=Prince Harry and Ms. Meghan Markle: Announcement of Titles |publisher=The Royal Family |date=May 19, 2018 |accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref> the first person to hold that title.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-sussex-44180674 |title=First Duke of Sussex was unlucky in love |date=May 19, 2018 |publisher= |via=www.bbc.com}}</ref> Following a decision to step back from royal duties, she and her husband have agreed not to use the style \"Royal Highness\" from early 2020, although they still retain the style.<ref>[https://sussexroyal.com/spring-2020-transition/ Sussex website]</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51163865|title=Harry and Meghan will not use HRH titles \u2013 palace|date=2020-01-18|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite newspaper | url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/18/harry-meghan-buckingham-palace-deal-analysis | title=Harry and Meghan sought a half-in half-out deal, but are \u2018out\u2019 | newspaper=[[The Guardian]] | author=Caroline Davies | date=18 January 2020 | accessdate=19 January 2020 | quote=Though Harry and Meghan still technically retain their HRH styles, they have agreed they will not use them. They have not been stripped of them, unlike Harry\u2019s mother Diana, Princess of Wales following her divorce.}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|name=the Duchess of Sussex\n|image= File:Coat of arms of Meghan, Duchess of Sussex.svg\n|imagesize=220\n|bannerimage=\n|badgeimage= \n|notes=Meghan bears the [[Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex#Arms|arms of her husband]] [[Impalement (heraldry)|impaled]] with her own. [[Thomas Woodcock (officer of arms)|Thomas Woodcock]], [[Garter King of Arms]], the senior officer of the [[College of Arms]], helped the Duchess with the design, which was approved by the Queen.<ref name=\"Royal-Arms\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.royal.uk/her-royal-highness-duchess-sussex-coat-arms |title=Her Royal Highness The Duchess of Sussex: Coat of Arms |date=May 25, 2018 |work=The Royal Family|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC-Arms\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-44258461 |title=Royal Wedding 2018: Meghan Markle coat of arms revealed |publisher=BBC |date=May 29, 2018 |accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref>\n|year_adopted=May 25, 2018\n|coronet= [[Coronet]] of a child of the heir apparent<ref name=\"Royal-Arms\"/>\n|torse=\n|helm=\n|escutcheon=[[quartering (heraldry)|Quarterly]] 1st and 4th [[Gules]] three lions [[passant guardant]] in pale [[Or (heraldry)|Or]] armed and langed [[Azure (heraldry)|Azure]] (England), 2nd Or a lion rampant Gules armed and langued Azure within a double [[tressure]] flory counterflory (Scotland), 3rd Azure a harp Or stringed [[Argent]] (Ireland), the whole differenced by a [[Label (heraldry)|label]] of five points Argent, the first, third and fifth points charged with an [[escallop]] Gules (Prince Harry); Impaled with a shield Azure a feather [[bendwise]] Argent quilled Or between two [[bendlet]]s Or all between two like feathers Argent quilled Or (Markle).<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-royals-meghan-heraldry/pacific-ocean-features-in-new-royal-markles-coat-of-arms-idUSKCN1IQ1ZL |title=Pacific Ocean features in new royal Markle's Coat of Arms |date=May 25, 2018 |work=Reuters|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref>\n|supporters= On the [[dexter and sinister|dexter]] side the lion used as a supporter by the Duke of Sussex and to the [[dexter and sinister|sinister]] a songbird Argent wings spread, [[:wikt:unguled|unguled]] Or and [[:wikt:gorged|gorged]] with the coronet of the Duke of Sussex.\n|compartment= Below the shield, a mount of grass with [[golden poppies]] and [[Chimonanthus praecox|wintersweet]] in flower.\n|motto=\n|orders=\n|banner=\n|badge=\n|symbolism=The blue background of the shield represents the [[Pacific Ocean]] off the [[California]] coast, while the two golden rays across the shield are symbolic of the sunshine of the Duchess's home state. The three quills represent communication and the power of words. Beneath the shield on the grass sits a collection of golden poppies, California's state flower, and wintersweet, which grows at Kensington Palace. The songbird with wings elevated as if flying and an open beak represents the power of communication.<ref name=\"Royal-Arms\"/><ref name=\"BBC-Arms\"/>\n}}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[General Hospital]]''\n| Jill\n| 1 episode<ref name=\"ABC SID\"/><ref name=\"Vulture\"/>\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Century City (TV series)|Century City]]''\n| Natasha\n| 1 episode \"A Mind is a Terrible Thing to Lose\" (season 1: episode 4)\n|-\n|2005\n| ''[[Cuts (TV series)|Cuts]]''\n| Cori\n| 1 episode \"My Boyfriend's Back\" (season 1: episode 5)\n|-\n|2005\n| ''[[Love, Inc. (TV series)|Love, Inc.]]''\n| Teresa Santos\n| 1 episode \"One on One\" (season 1: episode 9)\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[1 vs. 100]]''\n| Herself\n| 1 episode Mob member number 7\n|-\n|2006\n| ''[[The War at Home (TV series)|The War at Home]]''\n| Susan\n| 1 episode \"The Seventeen-Year Itch\" (season 1: episode 17)\n|-\n|2006\n| ''[[CSI: NY]]''\n| Veronica Perez\n| 1 episode \"Murder Sings the Blues\" (season 3: episode 7)\n|-\n|2006\n| ''Deceit''\n| Gwen\n| Television movie\n|-\n|\n| ''[[Deal or No Deal (U.S. game show)|Deal or No Deal]]''\n| Herself\n| Holder of Case #24; 34 episodes<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/meghan-markle-deal-deal-suitcase-model-happened-rest/ |title=Meghan Markle was a Deal or No Deal suitcase model \u2013 so what happened to the rest of them? |first=Cara |last=McGooran |date=November 30, 2017 |publisher=Telegraph Media Group Limited |location=London |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180413110911/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/meghan-markle-deal-deal-suitcase-model-happened-rest/ |archivedate=April 13, 2018 |df=}}</ref>\n